<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">What is Auto Alt-Text Generation?</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  When you upload an image to the Media Library, <strong><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ai/generative-ai/nova/" class="govuk-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Amazon Nova<span class="govuk-visually-hidden"> (opens in new tab)</span></a></strong>'s vision capabilities automatically analyse the image and generate a descriptive alt-text.
</p>

<div class="ndx-feature-highlight">
  <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Automatic and instant</h4>
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
    No extra clicks required. Simply upload an image and the alt-text field is automatically populated with an AI-generated description within seconds.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Why alt-text matters</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Alt-text (alternative text) is essential for web accessibility:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li><strong>Screen readers</strong> read alt-text aloud to visually impaired users</li>
  <li><strong>Search engines</strong> use alt-text to understand image content</li>
  <li><strong>Broken images</strong> display alt-text when images fail to load</li>
  <li><strong>WCAG compliance</strong> requires meaningful alt-text for all informative images</li>
</ul>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
    <strong>WCAG guideline:</strong> Alt-text should be concise (under 125 characters) and describe the image's content or purpose, not just "image of..." or "photo of...".
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">How to use Auto Alt-Text</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Go to the Media Library</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click Content &gt; Media &gt; Add media &gt; Image
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Upload an image</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click "Add a new file" and select an image from your computer
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Wait for AI analysis</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ai/generative-ai/nova/" class="govuk-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Amazon Nova<span class="govuk-visually-hidden"> (opens in new tab)</span></a> analyses the image and generates alt-text automatically
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Review and edit if needed</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The alt-text field is populated automatically. You can edit it if needed before saving.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

